1
00:00:09,067 --> 00:00:12,133
<i>You thought I'd agree
to be your mistress?</i>

2
00:00:12,267 --> 00:00:15,067
<i>I'm begging you,
just stay away from me!</i>

3
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:16,600
<i> You always leave me hanging.</i>

4
00:00:16,733 --> 00:00:18,767
<i>It's been a while since
the last time, you know.</i>

5
00:00:18,900 --> 00:00:20,767
<i>Good thing we didn't get caught.</i>

6
00:00:20,900 --> 00:00:21,900
<i> Let's make it quick, okay?</i>

7
00:00:22,033 --> 00:00:23,500
<i>Wow, you look like you're really
enjoying that.</i>

8
00:00:23,633 --> 00:00:25,233
<i> It's just breakfast.</i>

9
00:00:25,367 --> 00:00:27,100
<i>Just being appreciative
of the blessings, Mom.</i>

10
00:00:27,233 --> 00:00:28,767
<i> Just let them eat in peace.</i>

11
00:00:28,900 --> 00:00:32,500
<i>Anyway, Dad, I'm hosting
an open house tomorrow</i>

12
00:00:32,633 --> 00:00:33,867
<i> at the Menagerie.</i>

13
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:37,433
<i>It's to invite more potential
clients to buy units there.</i>

14
00:00:37,600 --> 00:00:39,467
<i> Love, can I come with you?</i>

15
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:41,733
<i>I don't have a choice
but to help Paolo.</i>

16
00:00:41,867 --> 00:00:44,967
<i>If the company does well,
we all benefit, right?</i>

17
00:00:45,100 --> 00:00:48,067
<i>I just wish, for once,
I could feel that.</i>

18
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:49,200
<i>Like you actually believe in me.</i>

19
00:00:49,333 --> 00:00:51,367
<i>Because maybe you forgot,
I'm your husband.</i>

20
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:52,300
<i> Not him.</i>

21
00:00:53,967 --> 00:00:55,233
<i> Drama!</i>

22
00:00:56,900 --> 00:00:58,967
Are you okay?

23
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:03,600
I'm okay, sis.

24
00:01:03,733 --> 00:01:04,933
You should go now.

25
00:01:05,067 --> 00:01:06,533
You might be late.

26
00:01:06,667 --> 00:01:08,500
Good Brother will get mad.

27
00:01:08,667 --> 00:01:09,433
Okay.

28
00:01:11,533 --> 00:01:15,167
Marj, don't worry
about Jobert and me.

29
00:01:15,300 --> 00:01:17,867
We've got this.

30
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:20,767
We'll help the nurse take
care of Jasmine

31
00:01:20,900 --> 00:01:22,300
while you're gone, okay?

32
00:01:22,433 --> 00:01:23,400
Go with your husband.

33
00:01:23,533 --> 00:01:24,767
Go with Paolo.

34
00:01:24,900 --> 00:01:28,433
I'm really glad you're here.

35
00:01:30,333 --> 00:01:31,633
Yes, that's for sure, Marj.

36
00:01:31,767 --> 00:01:33,133
I love you.

37
00:01:33,267 --> 00:01:35,500
I love you, sis.

38
00:01:35,633 --> 00:01:36,867
- Okay. Bye, Mom.
- You're so pretty.

39
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,533
- Bye!
- Be safe.

40
00:01:40,933 --> 00:01:41,900
So?

41
00:01:43,567 --> 00:01:45,700
Come on, Jobert,
let's get you dressed.

42
00:01:45,833 --> 00:01:46,867
You smell sweaty.

43
00:01:48,667 --> 00:01:51,467
I haven't
showered yet, Mom.

44
00:02:02,733 --> 00:02:03,933
Who could this be from?

45
00:02:06,833 --> 00:02:08,867
Could this be from Marj?

46
00:02:10,467 --> 00:02:11,433
Marj...

47
00:02:22,933 --> 00:02:24,233
Thank you.

48
00:03:31,867 --> 00:03:33,767
Congratulations, love.

49
00:03:34,633 --> 00:03:36,633
Looks like the
event's a success.

50
00:03:38,100 --> 00:03:39,000
Let's hope so.

51
00:03:42,367 --> 00:03:44,933
Maybe after this,
we can celebrate?

52
00:03:50,033 --> 00:03:53,500
Marj, this isn't a date.

53
00:03:54,433 --> 00:03:55,933
We're here for work.

54
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:58,167
Can we just focus on that?

55
00:04:04,900 --> 00:04:06,033
Hi!

56
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:08,467
Enjoying yourself?

57
00:04:09,167 --> 00:04:09,967
Good.

58
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,000
Hi, Marj!

59
00:04:16,700 --> 00:04:18,233
I'll give you this.

60
00:04:18,367 --> 00:04:20,633
You look presentablen tonight.

61
00:04:20,767 --> 00:04:24,467
But the question is,
can you still keep up socially?

62
00:04:25,333 --> 00:04:28,833
I mean, you've been stuck
at home

63
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:30,300
or in the hospital so long.

64
00:04:31,967 --> 00:04:35,933
You know, no matter how long
I've been out of the scene,

65
00:04:36,067 --> 00:04:38,800
I never forget my manners.

66
00:04:40,833 --> 00:04:43,600
It's hard when all you've
got going for you is looks

67
00:04:43,733 --> 00:04:45,433
but no class.

68
00:04:45,567 --> 00:04:48,333
Guess that's what happens
when you're full of envy.

69
00:04:49,667 --> 00:04:54,200
No matter how expensive
your outfit is,

70
00:04:54,333 --> 00:04:56,900
no matter how put-together
you look,

71
00:04:57,033 --> 00:05:04,933
it'll still show that you're
cheap because of your attitude.

72
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:11,233
Ladies, this is not the right
time or place for that.

73
00:05:11,367 --> 00:05:12,267
Please.

74
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:15,433
And you?

75
00:05:15,567 --> 00:05:16,600
What are you doing here?

76
00:05:18,167 --> 00:05:19,433
Why?

77
00:05:19,567 --> 00:05:21,100
Are you scared
I'll ruin your event?

78
00:05:22,500 --> 00:05:24,067
You don't have what it takes,
brother.

79
00:05:31,900 --> 00:05:32,633
Let's go.

80
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:44,333
Thank you.

81
00:05:49,633 --> 00:05:53,767
Hey, not just me.

82
00:05:53,900 --> 00:05:55,133
Take pictures of Marj, too.

83
00:05:55,267 --> 00:05:57,133
She hardly ever leaves
the house.

84
00:06:03,167 --> 00:06:04,300
Marj!

85
00:06:04,433 --> 00:06:06,233
Is that you?

86
00:06:06,367 --> 00:06:07,867
Long time no see!

87
00:06:08,033 --> 00:06:09,700
Mrs. Sutherland.

88
00:06:09,833 --> 00:06:10,633
How are you?

89
00:06:10,767 --> 00:06:11,900
I'm good.

90
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:17,767
Everyone, meet Marj.

91
00:06:19,300 --> 00:06:20,800
Hello, good evening.

92
00:06:20,933 --> 00:06:22,200
Thank you for coming.

93
00:06:22,333 --> 00:06:24,367
Thank you, thank you.
This is my husband, Paolo.

94
00:06:24,500 --> 00:06:25,633
Hello, good evening.

95
00:06:27,900 --> 00:06:30,167
She's the one I was
telling you about.

96
00:06:30,300 --> 00:06:32,433
If you're looking for a
great business partner,

97
00:06:32,567 --> 00:06:33,533
she's the one to talk to.

98
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,700
<i> Want attention?</i>

99
00:06:36,833 --> 00:06:37,800
<i> You got it.</i>

100
00:06:37,933 --> 00:06:39,167
<i> I'll make you go viral.</i>

101
00:06:44,333 --> 00:06:47,333
This Menagerie Manor
is the ultimate statement

102
00:06:47,467 --> 00:06:48,467
of luxury.

103
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:49,600
It's an exclusive enclave

104
00:06:49,733 --> 00:06:53,933
for those who can truly
afford it.

105
00:06:54,067 --> 00:06:55,800
Wow, I'm convinced.

106
00:06:55,933 --> 00:06:58,067
It really does seem like
a great place to live.

107
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:00,300
It feels so first-class, right?

108
00:07:00,433 --> 00:07:01,233
I know.

109
00:07:03,067 --> 00:07:04,933
Ma'am, who made that?

110
00:07:05,067 --> 00:07:07,900
Oh, this?

111
00:07:08,033 --> 00:07:12,133
The late Aurel Calma
designed it.

112
00:07:12,267 --> 00:07:13,100
Yeah.

113
00:07:13,233 --> 00:07:16,167
Chicken cages inspired him.

114
00:07:16,333 --> 00:07:17,767
And I'd love to show you more.

115
00:07:17,900 --> 00:07:19,800
There are more designs
at the back.

116
00:07:52,467 --> 00:07:55,733
You really are like a knight
in shining armor, Paolo.

117
00:07:55,867 --> 00:07:56,967
You're lucky, Marj.

118
00:07:57,100 --> 00:07:59,133
You have a husband who's ready
to save you!

119
00:07:59,267 --> 00:08:00,300
Yeah.

120
00:08:00,433 --> 00:08:01,933
Marj, are you okay?

121
00:08:03,567 --> 00:08:04,867
I'm fine.

122
00:08:07,700 --> 00:08:08,800
Sorry.

123
00:08:21,867 --> 00:08:22,667
Are you okay?

124
00:08:25,333 --> 00:08:27,167
Greg, I can't accept this.

125
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:31,467
I won't take it if you
give me another gift.

126
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:33,300
I don't need it.

127
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:37,800
My eyes are so annoying!

128
00:08:43,667 --> 00:08:45,800
It's like I'm agreeing

129
00:08:45,933 --> 00:08:49,300
to whatever you want to happen
if I accept this.

130
00:09:02,833 --> 00:09:05,533
I don't see anything wrong
with what I did, Evelyn.

131
00:09:06,800 --> 00:09:09,667
Your whole life,
you've endured a husband

132
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:12,767
who gave you nothing
but pain and heartbreak.

133
00:09:15,433 --> 00:09:19,367
I just want you to feel
that you deserve more.

134
00:09:21,167 --> 00:09:23,333
You're a special woman, Evelyn.

135
00:09:24,533 --> 00:09:26,100
I want you to understand that.

136
00:09:30,767 --> 00:09:32,533
No, no, no...

137
00:09:32,667 --> 00:09:34,500
I won't take it.

138
00:09:34,633 --> 00:09:36,567
And I'll give you more.

139
00:09:37,900 --> 00:09:40,767
I'll give you everything
you need.

140
00:09:40,900 --> 00:09:42,233
Everything you want.

141
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:46,867
I'll give you everything
your husband never gave you.

142
00:09:50,867 --> 00:09:52,033
You're crazy.

143
00:09:53,533 --> 00:09:58,667
I'm sorry,
but I don't want this, Greg.

144
00:09:59,433 --> 00:10:01,767
You're asking for trouble.

145
00:10:04,133 --> 00:10:07,800
It won't be trouble,
not if we keep it a secret.

146
00:10:09,267 --> 00:10:10,767
We'll figure it out.

147
00:10:16,233 --> 00:10:18,833
I don't want to add
to Marj's problems.

148
00:10:20,300 --> 00:10:22,267
I already let her down once,
Greg.

149
00:10:23,567 --> 00:10:24,767
So no more.

150
00:10:26,400 --> 00:10:28,533
Stop it, Greg.

151
00:10:28,667 --> 00:10:29,533
Enough.

152
00:10:33,733 --> 00:10:34,933
Oh my.

153
00:10:35,100 --> 00:10:37,633
Ma'am Evelyn is up to something.

154
00:10:38,800 --> 00:10:40,733
Who could she be with?

155
00:10:40,867 --> 00:10:43,133
Who's that guy?

156
00:10:53,967 --> 00:10:55,467
Are you sure you're okay?

157
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:57,233
Maybe we should get
that checked.

158
00:10:58,867 --> 00:10:59,967
I'm fine.

159
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:03,067
Thanks for catching me earlier.

160
00:11:05,067 --> 00:11:07,600
Actually, I'm really happy.

161
00:11:07,767 --> 00:11:11,933
Because it felt like the old
Paolo came back.

162
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:15,667
The one who always saves me.

163
00:11:16,700 --> 00:11:18,300
The one who catches me

164
00:11:18,433 --> 00:11:21,000
when I feel like
I'm about to fall.

165
00:11:23,500 --> 00:11:25,600
I really missed that
version of you.

166
00:11:30,100 --> 00:11:31,667
Sir Paolo, excuse me.

167
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:35,000
Mr. Ang, North Group's chairman,
wants to speak with you.

168
00:11:35,133 --> 00:11:39,000
He wants to discuss the price
points of Menagerie Manor.

169
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:43,933
Sorry, I have to go.

170
00:11:57,867 --> 00:12:00,133
Gosh. You almost fell earlier.

171
00:12:01,100 --> 00:12:02,200
Are you hurt?

172
00:12:02,333 --> 00:12:03,767
I'm fine.

173
00:12:03,900 --> 00:12:05,867
Good thing nothing bad happened.

174
00:12:07,933 --> 00:12:10,267
It wasn't an accident.

175
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:12,233
It seemed that she
did it on purpose.

176
00:12:12,367 --> 00:12:14,200
What?

177
00:12:14,333 --> 00:12:15,167
Why?

178
00:12:17,967 --> 00:12:19,367
Someone did it on purpose.

179
00:12:20,467 --> 00:12:21,567
On purpose?

180
00:12:22,833 --> 00:12:24,667
Who would do that?

181
00:12:26,367 --> 00:12:27,567
It's Thea.

182
00:12:30,367 --> 00:12:31,767
Just follow what I told you.

183
00:12:31,900 --> 00:12:33,967
Why do I have to explain
everything?

184
00:12:35,667 --> 00:12:37,033
Fine, whatever.

185
00:12:41,067 --> 00:12:43,633
Just finish your assignments
and go to bed!

186
00:12:43,767 --> 00:12:46,200
Stop wasting time on Jasmine.

187
00:12:46,333 --> 00:12:47,533
Do you understand?

188
00:12:47,700 --> 00:12:49,067
<i> Yes, Mommy.</i>

189
00:12:54,433 --> 00:12:56,200
All right, I'll head downstairs.

190
00:12:56,333 --> 00:12:59,533
I still need to take care
of some clients.

191
00:12:59,667 --> 00:13:02,333
The air suddenly got
kind of weird out here.

192
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:07,067
Hi, Marj.

193
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:08,867
Did you come here to rest

194
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:12,567
after that embarrassing
performance earlier?

195
00:13:14,133 --> 00:13:17,600
Looks like you need to step out
of the spotlight for a bit.

196
00:13:17,733 --> 00:13:21,467
Remember,
we're selling the house.

197
00:13:21,633 --> 00:13:25,767
Not your pity-party,
victim-act performance.

198
00:13:25,900 --> 00:13:28,100
Just be straight with me, Thea.

199
00:13:28,233 --> 00:13:30,833
Did you spill wine on the floor?

200
00:13:30,967 --> 00:13:33,300
Did you actually try
to humiliate me?

201
00:13:33,433 --> 00:13:34,667
Me? Seriously?

202
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:37,100
Isn't it possible
you're just clumsy?

203
00:13:37,233 --> 00:13:41,300
You always blame me on every bad
thing that happens to you.

204
00:13:41,433 --> 00:13:44,233
You're accusing me
without any proof.

205
00:13:44,367 --> 00:13:45,333
None?

206
00:13:45,467 --> 00:13:48,933
Mrs. Sutherland saw you
holding a wine glass.

207
00:13:49,067 --> 00:13:50,033
Of course, I was.

208
00:13:50,167 --> 00:13:51,100
It's a party.

209
00:13:51,233 --> 00:13:52,733
Everyone's drinking.

210
00:13:52,867 --> 00:13:55,067
Why don't you suspect them?

211
00:13:55,233 --> 00:13:56,233
It could be anyone.

212
00:13:56,367 --> 00:13:57,533
Yes, it could be anyone.

213
00:13:57,667 --> 00:13:59,700
But there's only one person
who hates me.

214
00:13:59,833 --> 00:14:00,967
And that's you.

215
00:14:01,100 --> 00:14:03,967
Even at home, all you ever do
is provoke me.

216
00:14:04,100 --> 00:14:07,000
You're obsessed
with bringing me down.

217
00:14:07,133 --> 00:14:08,333
Oh, wow.

218
00:14:08,467 --> 00:14:10,333
You're so full of yourself.

219
00:14:10,467 --> 00:14:12,533
Why would I waste my time
on you?

220
00:14:13,233 --> 00:14:16,333
It's not my fault you don't
watch where you're going.

221
00:14:18,833 --> 00:14:20,633
You did that on purpose!

222
00:14:20,767 --> 00:14:22,167
You really want
to start something?

223
00:14:27,267 --> 00:14:28,667
I swear I'll rip your hair out!

224
00:14:28,833 --> 00:14:30,767
Just like your fake extensions!

225
00:14:34,667 --> 00:14:35,500
Darn you!

226
00:14:38,100 --> 00:14:40,433
Why are you so worked up
over me?

227
00:14:40,567 --> 00:14:42,033
You brat!

228
00:14:42,167 --> 00:14:43,267
You fake!

229
00:14:52,067 --> 00:14:53,033
There!

230
00:14:53,167 --> 00:14:54,300
Get a grip!

231
00:15:04,900 --> 00:15:06,333
Darn you, you witch!

232
00:15:06,467 --> 00:15:07,667
You have no shame!

233
00:15:16,133 --> 00:15:17,567
Oh my God, Marj!
Oh my God, Marj!

234
00:15:17,700 --> 00:15:19,067
Stop it! Stop fighting!

235
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:20,467
That's embarrassing!
There are people outside!

236
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:22,033
I'm just teaching her a lesson!

237
00:15:22,167 --> 00:15:24,800
She's a fake! A brat!

238
00:15:24,933 --> 00:15:26,400
Don't speak to me in Visayan!

239
00:15:26,533 --> 00:15:28,900
If you're going to curse me out,
do it in Tagalog!

240
00:15:31,433 --> 00:15:33,667
Help!

241
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:37,067
Help!

242
00:15:40,500 --> 00:15:41,600
Yes, sir.

243
00:15:41,733 --> 00:15:44,067
The Menagerie units are
positioned as legacy properties.

244
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:45,633
Excuse me.

245
00:15:45,767 --> 00:15:46,633
Paolo.

246
00:15:46,767 --> 00:15:49,267
[Speaking in Visayan]

247
00:15:49,400 --> 00:15:50,933
What is it?

248
00:15:51,067 --> 00:15:52,467
You need to go upstairs
right now.

249
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:54,267
Marj and Thea are fighting.

250
00:16:07,533 --> 00:16:08,167
Thea!

251
00:16:08,333 --> 00:16:10,067
Thea!

252
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:10,800
- What? Stop it!

253
00:16:10,933 --> 00:16:11,833
Both of you, stop!

254
00:16:17,567 --> 00:16:18,833
That's enough!

255
00:16:18,967 --> 00:16:19,967
Marj, Marj!

256
00:16:20,100 --> 00:16:21,067
Stop it! Stop!

257
00:16:25,233 --> 00:16:26,633
Let go of my wife!

258
00:16:27,967 --> 00:16:29,033
I'm just trying to break it up!

259
00:16:30,767 --> 00:16:31,367
Paolo!

260
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:36,667
Paolo!

261
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:37,667
Edward!

262
00:16:40,633 --> 00:16:41,933
That's enough!

263
00:16:45,033 --> 00:16:46,100
Stop!

264
00:16:48,033 --> 00:16:49,467
- What the hell?
- Paolo, stop it!

265
00:16:54,867 --> 00:16:57,767
- Break it up!
- Stop them!

266
00:16:58,767 --> 00:17:01,333
Stop them!

267
00:17:21,433 --> 00:17:22,733
Who?

268
00:17:23,067 --> 00:17:24,467
Ma'am Evelyn?

269
00:17:24,600 --> 00:17:26,167
That's right.

270
00:17:26,300 --> 00:17:29,767
Ma'am Evelyn had someone
with her in the garden.

271
00:17:29,900 --> 00:17:31,967
A man.

272
00:17:32,100 --> 00:17:34,133
What? A man?

273
00:17:34,267 --> 00:17:35,267
Who was it?

274
00:17:35,400 --> 00:17:37,200
You keep asking!
I said it was a man.

275
00:17:37,333 --> 00:17:38,933
I didn't recognize him.

276
00:17:39,067 --> 00:17:40,600
My eyesight's not that great,
okay?

277
00:17:40,733 --> 00:17:42,733
And it was dark earlier.

278
00:17:42,867 --> 00:17:44,700
Wow, Manang Yolly...

279
00:17:44,833 --> 00:17:46,933
that story's such a tease.

280
00:17:47,067 --> 00:17:47,867
What do you want me to do?

281
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,467
I didn't see him clearly.

282
00:17:51,533 --> 00:17:54,033
Manang, maybe it was just
Jobert.

283
00:17:54,167 --> 00:17:56,333
Oh no, definitely not.

284
00:17:56,467 --> 00:17:59,300
I know how Jobert moves.

285
00:18:00,100 --> 00:18:01,400
That one was different.

286
00:18:02,567 --> 00:18:03,933
Like, something was going on.

287
00:18:04,633 --> 00:18:05,767
Something?

288
00:18:06,467 --> 00:18:07,967
That's crazy.

289
00:18:08,100 --> 00:18:10,800
But there's only one
explanation for that.

290
00:18:10,933 --> 00:18:15,467
Ma'am Evelyn is sneaking a man
into the mansion.

291
00:18:18,267 --> 00:18:20,167
Oh no, Manang.

292
00:18:20,300 --> 00:18:22,000
We should report this
to Ma'am Regina.

293
00:18:22,167 --> 00:18:23,167
Hold on.

294
00:18:23,300 --> 00:18:24,633
We're not sure yet.

295
00:18:24,767 --> 00:18:26,267
We might embarrass ourselves.

296
00:18:27,500 --> 00:18:28,233
- Manang.
- What?

297
00:18:28,367 --> 00:18:29,900
Then let's make sure.

298
00:18:30,033 --> 00:18:33,933
Or better yet, go get your eyes
checked first.

299
00:18:34,067 --> 00:18:35,367
Oh, so now you're making fun
of me?

300
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:38,867
Let's just investigate
who was with Ma'am Evelyn

301
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:40,800
in the garden earlier, okay?

302
00:18:40,933 --> 00:18:41,900
All right.

303
00:18:43,500 --> 00:18:47,500
I don't care if you tear
each other apart.

304
00:18:49,367 --> 00:18:51,233
Just don't do it
where anyone can see!

305
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:54,733
That was a public event.

306
00:18:54,900 --> 00:19:00,267
There were VIPs,
media, investors,

307
00:19:00,400 --> 00:19:02,533
and you turned it into a circus!

308
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:07,000
Greg, let's be fair.

309
00:19:07,133 --> 00:19:08,933
They're not the only ones
at fault.

310
00:19:09,067 --> 00:19:10,167
Marj started it.

311
00:19:10,300 --> 00:19:11,633
That's what Thea said.

312
00:19:11,767 --> 00:19:12,900
So what now?

313
00:19:13,033 --> 00:19:14,000
Happy?

314
00:19:14,133 --> 00:19:16,833
Because of you,
Paolo's sinking even deeper.

315
00:19:16,967 --> 00:19:19,167
How can you live with yourself?

316
00:19:19,300 --> 00:19:20,700
You really have the nerve
to twist things around

317
00:19:20,833 --> 00:19:22,200
in front of Mom and Dad.

318
00:19:22,333 --> 00:19:24,400
We both know who started
that mess.

319
00:19:24,533 --> 00:19:28,267
I don't care who started it.

320
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:29,867
They're the men.

321
00:19:30,033 --> 00:19:31,733
They should've handled
their wives.

322
00:19:33,533 --> 00:19:35,533
And another thing.

323
00:19:35,667 --> 00:19:38,867
You are the face of the company.

324
00:19:40,700 --> 00:19:42,167
Paolo may be running
the project,

325
00:19:42,300 --> 00:19:44,400
but after what you pulled,

326
00:19:44,533 --> 00:19:46,533
no one's going to want to buy
those houses!

327
00:19:46,667 --> 00:19:47,667
Does it even matter?

328
00:19:47,800 --> 00:19:48,967
The bottom line is,

329
00:19:49,100 --> 00:19:51,367
some of those people earlier
were supposed to be sure buyers.

330
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:53,433
But because of you, poof!

331
00:19:53,567 --> 00:19:54,267
They're gone.

332
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:56,300
Just like that.

333
00:19:56,433 --> 00:19:57,867
Listen to me.

334
00:19:58,000 --> 00:19:59,733
This is your last warning.

335
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:02,633
One more stunt like that,

336
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:04,700
and I will completely
disown you!

337
00:20:05,467 --> 00:20:06,400
You!

338
00:20:08,233 --> 00:20:11,667
Fix this mess,
if you want to stay as CEO!

339
00:20:14,500 --> 00:20:15,300
Yes, Dad.

340
00:20:26,533 --> 00:20:27,433
Paolo.

341
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:57,800
Pao...

342
00:20:59,200 --> 00:20:59,967
Pao...

343
00:21:00,633 --> 00:21:02,267
Paolo, I'm sorry.

344
00:21:02,400 --> 00:21:04,200
What's your apology
going to do now?

345
00:21:04,333 --> 00:21:05,300
It already happened.

346
00:21:05,433 --> 00:21:07,100
Love, I didn't mean
for that to happen.

347
00:21:07,233 --> 00:21:08,400
It was Thea.

348
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:11,233
Let me guess.

349
00:21:11,367 --> 00:21:14,467
Thea insulted you,
and you just reacted.

350
00:21:15,500 --> 00:21:17,533
Marj, you don't have to respond
to everything!

351
00:21:19,033 --> 00:21:20,133
I'll make it up to you.

352
00:21:21,600 --> 00:21:25,633
I'll figure out a way to sell
the Menagerie units.

353
00:21:27,733 --> 00:21:29,200
Marj, no.

354
00:21:29,333 --> 00:21:30,467
You've done enough.

355
00:21:31,600 --> 00:21:32,633
Just...

356
00:21:34,833 --> 00:21:36,967
go back to Jasmine.

357
00:21:37,100 --> 00:21:38,200
She needs you.

358
00:21:41,167 --> 00:21:44,633
As for work,
just leave it to me.

359
00:21:45,667 --> 00:21:46,533
Okay?

360
00:21:47,567 --> 00:21:48,733
Pao...

361
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:07,533
Oh my God, Edward!

362
00:22:07,667 --> 00:22:09,333
I don't know what to do anymore!

363
00:22:09,467 --> 00:22:10,900
Seriously.

364
00:22:11,033 --> 00:22:13,867
Why did you even go up
against your brother?

365
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:16,733
Now Dad's got an even worse
impression of you.

366
00:22:16,900 --> 00:22:18,567
When has he ever
liked me anyway?

367
00:22:18,700 --> 00:22:19,833
Exactly!

368
00:22:19,967 --> 00:22:22,133
And you just made it worse!

369
00:22:22,267 --> 00:22:23,133
Can you not?

370
00:22:24,167 --> 00:22:26,300
Hon, relax.

371
00:22:26,433 --> 00:22:28,500
It's not over yet.

372
00:22:28,633 --> 00:22:30,767
Soon, the tables will turn.

373
00:22:32,600 --> 00:22:33,467
What?

374
00:22:35,467 --> 00:22:36,833
You'll see.

375
00:22:36,967 --> 00:22:39,167
You'll find out who's really
better between Paolo and me.

376
00:22:39,300 --> 00:22:41,000
Just wait and see.

377
00:22:41,133 --> 00:22:42,933
The world goes around, hon.

378
00:22:43,067 --> 00:22:44,333
What's with the drama?

379
00:22:47,367 --> 00:22:49,200
Nothing.

380
00:22:49,367 --> 00:22:50,833
Just trust me.

381
00:22:50,967 --> 00:22:52,200
I'll figure this out.

382
00:23:14,933 --> 00:23:16,867
Wow, this is really good,
Ma'am Evelyn.

383
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:19,900
No wonder it's Ma'am Jasmine's
favorite.

384
00:23:20,033 --> 00:23:21,433
Oh, thank you.

385
00:23:21,600 --> 00:23:23,533
I added extra moringa leaves

386
00:23:23,667 --> 00:23:26,200
so it's more nutritious
for Jasmine.

387
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:33,500
Ma'am Evelyn,
your boyfriend is so lucky.

388
00:23:33,633 --> 00:23:37,267
Getting to eat food this good
every day.

389
00:23:37,400 --> 00:23:38,800
Oh, I'm not that great
at cooking.

390
00:23:38,933 --> 00:23:41,133
And I don't have a boyfriend.

391
00:23:44,733 --> 00:23:46,533
You don't?

392
00:23:46,667 --> 00:23:48,200
What about a suitor?

393
00:23:48,333 --> 00:23:50,133
None either.

394
00:23:50,267 --> 00:23:52,867
Ma'am Evelyn, no malice, okay?

395
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:54,833
I don't mean anything by it.

396
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:56,833
Do you really not want
to fall in love again?

397
00:23:56,967 --> 00:23:59,667
Ever since you
and your husband separated,

398
00:23:59,800 --> 00:24:02,900
have you not liked
any other man?

399
00:24:03,033 --> 00:24:04,667
No malice there, I swear.

400
00:24:06,533 --> 00:24:09,633
Wait, my grandchild needs me.

401
00:24:10,300 --> 00:24:11,633
I'll just bring this to her.

402
00:24:11,767 --> 00:24:13,967
Salve, get me some water.

403
00:24:14,100 --> 00:24:14,900
Okay, thanks.

404
00:24:15,033 --> 00:24:16,700
I'll leave you for now.

405
00:24:16,833 --> 00:24:17,800
Excuse me.

406
00:24:17,933 --> 00:24:18,833
Thank you.

407
00:24:27,567 --> 00:24:28,667
Confirmed!

408
00:24:28,833 --> 00:24:30,800
There's definitely something
going on!

409
00:24:30,933 --> 00:24:32,133
What do you mean "something"?

410
00:24:32,267 --> 00:24:32,867
Nothing.

411
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:34,133
Just eat your food.

412
00:24:40,167 --> 00:24:46,133
Maybe I shouldn't have told you
about my suspicion.

413
00:24:46,267 --> 00:24:47,933
You got into a fight with Thea
because of it.

414
00:24:49,033 --> 00:24:50,667
It's okay, Mrs. Sutherland.

415
00:24:50,800 --> 00:24:53,467
It was my decision
to confront her.

416
00:24:53,600 --> 00:24:55,133
It's not your fault.

417
00:24:55,267 --> 00:24:56,267
I'm sorry.

418
00:24:58,300 --> 00:25:00,100
How are you?

419
00:25:00,233 --> 00:25:01,400
Are you okay?

420
00:25:03,633 --> 00:25:06,300
Not really.

421
00:25:06,433 --> 00:25:11,933
No matter what I do to fix
my relationship with Paolo,

422
00:25:12,067 --> 00:25:15,567
it feels like I just made
everything worse.

423
00:25:19,433 --> 00:25:20,367
Let's eat.

424
00:25:21,500 --> 00:25:26,300
I really want to help
your husband out.

425
00:25:27,267 --> 00:25:31,767
But my husband said fifty
million is too expensive

426
00:25:31,900 --> 00:25:33,233
for a house.

427
00:25:34,767 --> 00:25:38,833
And Torrecampo Realty
isn't like a market

428
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:40,733
where you can ask
for a discount.

429
00:25:43,300 --> 00:25:44,333
A discount?

430
00:25:46,500 --> 00:25:49,067
Oh, Mrs. Sutherland,
thank you so much!

431
00:25:49,200 --> 00:25:50,767
Oh, thank you! Thank you!

432
00:25:54,267 --> 00:25:55,700
I can now help Paolo!

433
00:25:55,833 --> 00:25:57,133
Thank you!

434
00:25:59,300 --> 00:26:00,867
Why? What did I say?

435
00:26:05,967 --> 00:26:07,433
What did I say?

436
00:26:11,433 --> 00:26:12,600
Come on and eat.

437
00:26:20,300 --> 00:26:22,867
I'm starting to lose patience,
Edward.

438
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:27,700
You still haven't given me
anything useful against Paolo.

439
00:26:27,833 --> 00:26:30,333
What's so hard about what
I'm asking you to do?

440
00:26:30,467 --> 00:26:31,500
I just need you

441
00:26:31,633 --> 00:26:34,500
to access your brother's
personal computer.

442
00:26:34,633 --> 00:26:36,767
It's right there,
just a few feet away.

443
00:26:36,900 --> 00:26:40,933
And if Paolo's Menagerie
project succeeds,

444
00:26:41,067 --> 00:26:43,033
he's just going to get even more
praise from your dad.

445
00:26:43,200 --> 00:26:44,033
And you?

446
00:26:44,167 --> 00:26:46,567
You'll just keep
getting pushed aside.

447
00:26:46,700 --> 00:26:47,733
Is that what you want?

448
00:26:47,867 --> 00:26:49,400
You bastard, Paolo.

449
00:26:49,533 --> 00:26:52,367
You really had to do that
right in front of me.

450
00:26:52,500 --> 00:26:53,200
Hello?

451
00:26:53,333 --> 00:26:55,333
<i> Hello, who is this?</i>

452
00:26:55,467 --> 00:26:57,067
Is something wrong?

453
00:26:57,200 --> 00:26:59,067
Something happened last night.

454
00:26:59,200 --> 00:27:01,433
Someone called Paolo's phone.

455
00:27:01,567 --> 00:27:03,100
It was a woman's voice.

456
00:27:03,233 --> 00:27:06,067
But, Hannah, the voice
sounded familiar.

457
00:27:06,200 --> 00:27:09,167
Marj, don't get mad, okay?

458
00:27:09,300 --> 00:27:12,200
Could it be that Paolo is going
back to his old ways?

459
00:27:12,333 --> 00:27:14,367
Is your husband seeing
other women again?
